# Rust
V2RayDAR-main/target/
# Cargo.lock IS committed on purpose: v2raydar is a binary, not a library, and
# CI builds the released binary from it. Without the lockfile every build
# re-resolves dependencies to their newest semver-compatible versions, so a
# green build today can break tomorrow with no change on our side.

